  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Projet de renforcement du leadership feminin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For this project, local women in five provinces (Gitega, Muramuya, Ruyigi, Bubanza and Cankuzo) have been trained to take a leadership role in the process of peacebuilding. The objective is to contribute to an equal and effective participation of  women and men in decision making and conflict resolution on local level. This is achieved by training local women leaders and strengthening the local committees of women leaders. The project is closely aligned with the implementation of UNSCR 1325, for which Burundi has developed a National Action Plan.</narrative>
  </description>
